I think there is no any text input filters(ie. numbers only, 10 digits only, none empty...etc) in the front-end and the back-end side.
Due to no any input filters, infinite search requests will cost a lot of server resource and cost.
Hackers are easy to attack the service such as DDos, DDDos attack.
Add a button disable click function when the input text is empty.
Using placeholder to add some input hint below the input text.
Add a reCaptcha can also make webside safer and hackers will need more effort to attack.
